1
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:09,840
I'm Ryuugamine Mikado.

2
00:01:09,840 --> 00:01:10,790
Whoa!

3
00:01:10,790 --> 00:01:12,710
Is it really you, Kida-kun?!

4
00:01:12,710 --> 00:01:14,550
There aren't as many color gang members as before.

5
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:18,550
Most of them got arrested for starting a gang war in Saitama.

6
00:01:18,910 --> 00:01:19,970
I'm Sonohara Anri.

7
00:01:20,860 --> 00:01:22,430
Nice to meet you all.

8
00:01:22,430 --> 00:01:23,430
Harima-san!

9
00:01:24,180 --> 00:01:25,240
I'm sorry! I thought you were someone else!

10
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,230
If you pledge to be a bona fide Ikebukuronian,

11
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:29,310
you will overcome this ordeal!

12
00:01:30,020 --> 00:01:31,120
I found...

13
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:32,530
my love!

14
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:12,860
I-I'm sorry!

15
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:14,650
Really!

16
00:02:15,050 --> 00:02:16,730
I'll give it back! So please!

17
00:02:17,620 --> 00:02:18,950
Please forgive me.

18
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:40,590
Sheesh!

19
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,510
I'm really pissed!

20
00:02:44,330 --> 00:02:46,270
It's my fault, Selty.

21
00:02:46,270 --> 00:02:48,850
It's all because I accepted such a stupid job.

22
00:02:49,790 --> 00:02:52,560
The job itself was supposed to be quick.

23
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:56,020
But then that thing just appeared.

24
00:03:10,370 --> 00:03:11,580
You are not human!

25
00:03:11,580 --> 00:03:13,250
Monster! Monster!

26
00:03:13,250 --> 00:03:14,380
You monster!

27
00:03:15,190 --> 00:03:17,210
You heard voices from your wound?

28
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:19,720
They called me a monster!

29
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:21,500
How rude!

30
00:03:21,500 --> 00:03:23,610
They could have at least called you a "devil woman" or something.

31
00:03:23,610 --> 00:03:24,840
What the hell was that thing?

32
00:03:28,060 --> 00:03:29,980
What do I do if it's an alien?!

33
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:32,480
Selty...

34
00:03:33,140 --> 00:03:35,130
Am I supposed to laugh about this?

35
00:03:37,300 --> 00:03:39,070
M-Monster!

36
00:03:42,970 --> 00:03:43,570
Let's go!

37
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:51,530
Apparently, this city is made of jokes, coincidences, and whims.

38
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:05,230
This situation might be a result of God's whims, or maybe it's just one of his jokes.

39
00:04:05,840 --> 00:04:09,220
I fell in love at first sight with 37 girls during the opening ceremony,

40
00:04:09,220 --> 00:04:12,230
and even though I'm going home with the bespectacled girl that's in my top five,

41
00:04:12,230 --> 00:04:16,650
because of some development that would put soap operas to shame...

42
00:04:16,650 --> 00:04:19,180
the mood's ruined by some dumbass.

43
00:04:19,180 --> 00:04:20,370
Screw this...

44
00:04:22,020 --> 00:04:23,870
It was pretty hectic last time, right?

45
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:25,450
Y-Yeah.

46
00:04:31,370 --> 00:04:33,380
This ain't going anywhere.

47
00:04:33,380 --> 00:04:35,860
Dude, you really surprised me back then.

48
00:04:35,860 --> 00:04:37,880
I didn't expect you to take the initiative.

49
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:40,130
Th-That's not true!

50
00:04:42,010 --> 00:04:43,610
No way! Mikado!

51
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:45,420
But in the end, you saved me.

52
00:04:45,420 --> 00:04:49,320
I wouldn't have wasted such an opportunity if I were in your shoes.

53
00:04:49,320 --> 00:04:53,140
By now, we'd be in WGP talking so romantically about love...

54
00:04:54,040 --> 00:04:55,520
So please go out with me!

55
00:04:56,790 --> 00:04:57,520
Kida-kun!

56
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:58,750
Um... I—

57
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:01,420
Nah, you don't have to reply right now.

58
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:03,550
I'm waiting on a reply from seven other girls,

59
00:05:03,550 --> 00:05:05,530
and I'm trying to make up my mind on who to date.

60
00:05:05,530 --> 00:05:08,660
Sonohara-san, you don't have to take him seriously.

61
00:05:08,660 --> 00:05:10,210
You'll just wear yourself out.

62
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:13,550
Plus he talks like a big playboy, but he's really just a peanut.

63
00:05:13,550 --> 00:05:14,840
Even when he hits on girls—

64
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:16,100
Hey, Mikado!

65
00:05:19,410 --> 00:05:22,580
This guy, known as Ryuugamine Mikado, is my best friend.

66
00:05:22,580 --> 00:05:25,170
It's only been a couple of days since he came to Ikebukuro.

67
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:29,080
He's an honest, naïve guy with an unexpected stubborn side.

68
00:05:29,080 --> 00:05:31,180
Thus, I just can't leave him alone.

69
00:05:31,180 --> 00:05:34,890
And I'm stuck in a love triangle with this pure-hearted boy.

70
00:05:34,890 --> 00:05:36,940
Is this what they call "youth"?

71
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,940
You two seem to get along pretty well.

72
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:43,630
Of course.

73
00:05:43,630 --> 00:05:45,530
We're so close we're inseparable.

74
00:05:46,900 --> 00:05:49,360
To explain this situation...

75
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,580
We have to go back to the opening ceremony.

76
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,010
I'm Yagiri Seiji.

77
00:05:56,010 --> 00:05:57,710
Nice to meet you all.

78
00:05:57,710 --> 00:06:02,020
Take your seat, Yagiri.

79
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,000
I won't.

80
00:06:03,710 --> 00:06:07,150
I don't think I'll be able to come to school for a while.

81
00:06:07,150 --> 00:06:10,390
Nah, perhaps I'll never come back.

82
00:06:11,370 --> 00:06:15,210
I have to take care of something very important to me.

83
00:06:15,210 --> 00:06:17,990
I can't deal with you people.

84
00:06:17,990 --> 00:06:19,770
Bye.

85
00:06:19,770 --> 00:06:21,400
H-Hey, Yagiri!

86
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,210
Wait!

87
00:06:22,210 --> 00:06:23,730
Wait, I said!

88
00:06:23,730 --> 00:06:26,540
I thought, "There are so many weirdos running around,"

89
00:06:26,540 --> 00:06:27,200
Yagiri! Wait!
I thought, "There are so many weirdos running around,"

90
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,530
when Mikado told me about it.
Yagiri! Wait!

91
00:06:28,530 --> 00:06:29,240
when Mikado told me about it.

92
00:06:30,370 --> 00:06:31,530
Please wait!

93
00:06:31,530 --> 00:06:34,800
That was literally the moment when I fell in love.

94
00:06:34,800 --> 00:06:37,540
My heart gave a big ba-dump when I saw her cute smile.

95
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:39,710
Oh wait, she didn't smile.

96
00:06:39,710 --> 00:06:41,250
Leave me alone!

97
00:06:41,250 --> 00:06:42,000
Wait!

98
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:43,290
Hey.

99
00:06:43,290 --> 00:06:44,780
Is something wrong?

100
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:54,950
And thus she claimed the top spot of my "girls I'm gonna make my girlfriend" list.

101
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:55,680
And today...

102
00:07:00,460 --> 00:07:02,080
Hey, Sonohara.

103
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,420
Are you heading home?

104
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:06,360
Yes.

105
00:07:07,980 --> 00:07:09,900
Say, Sonohara.

106
00:07:09,900 --> 00:07:12,730
Is something bothering you?

107
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:17,060
You aren't in trouble, or getting bullied, are you?

108
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:17,990
No.

109
00:07:17,990 --> 00:07:20,790
Come talk to me if something happens.

110
00:07:22,310 --> 00:07:23,480
I'm fine.

111
00:07:24,130 --> 00:07:25,470
Well, if you say so.

112
00:07:25,470 --> 00:07:28,160
Oh yeah, Harima still hasn't come back?

113
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:30,470
You two were in the same class back then.

114
00:07:31,290 --> 00:07:35,970
It wasn't easy to get you two in the same class here too.

115
00:07:35,970 --> 00:07:40,660
Your junior high teacher, Saitou-sensei, told me to take good care of you.

116
00:07:40,660 --> 00:07:43,490
So you don't have to be polite with me, okay?

117
00:07:43,490 --> 00:07:46,940
Oh yeah, I'll give you a ride home.

118
00:07:46,940 --> 00:07:47,980
Did you hear about it?

119
00:07:47,980 --> 00:07:51,050
There was another slasher incident in Ikebukuro.

120
00:07:52,860 --> 00:07:54,990
Whoa, Nasujima-sensei, is that sexual harassment I see there?

121
00:07:57,240 --> 00:08:01,430
Wowzers! You even made the timid, pure, bespectacled class rep moan.

122
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:05,040
This is literally sexual harassment, isn't it?

123
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:08,040
Or with a Russian accent, "Sexy kharasho"?

124
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:10,430
Cut that out, Kida!

125
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:13,880
Sonohara, don't get the wrong idea and start silly rumors.

126
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:16,960
Does she look like such a frivolous girl?

127
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,510
Yeah, she doesn't.

128
00:08:18,510 --> 00:08:19,890
Seriously, you have to tone your jokes down.

129
00:08:20,680 --> 00:08:24,230
No worries. I'll be the one spreading the rumors.

130
00:08:28,250 --> 00:08:30,560
I guess I was like a Champion of Justice.

131
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:32,280
Shit, that was so cool of me.

132
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:34,290
She's so gonna be head-over-heels for me.

133
00:08:34,860 --> 00:08:35,670
Kida-kun?

134
00:08:35,670 --> 00:08:36,620
Sonohara-san?

135
00:08:36,620 --> 00:08:39,620
Nice fucking timing.

136
00:08:44,380 --> 00:08:45,620
Sorry for the wait.

137
00:08:46,050 --> 00:08:47,170
Here you go.

138
00:08:47,170 --> 00:08:48,460
Thanks.

139
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,670
Hey, you should really watch out.

140
00:08:54,080 --> 00:08:57,680
Most of the rumors about Nasujima are just that,

141
00:08:57,680 --> 00:09:00,790
but it's true that he went after a student:

142
00:09:00,790 --> 00:09:03,410
A sophomore named Niekawa Haruna.

143
00:09:03,410 --> 00:09:05,960
She transferred out during second semester last year.

144
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:10,270
People almost found out that she was dating Nasujima.

145
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:11,450
Are you serious?

146
00:09:11,450 --> 00:09:14,370
It's unknown if she made the decision herself, if she was threatened by Nasujima,

147
00:09:14,370 --> 00:09:17,110
or if the school forced her to transfer.

148
00:09:17,620 --> 00:09:20,940
Well, if anything happens, Mikado and I will save you.

149
00:09:20,940 --> 00:09:21,790
Right, Mikado?

150
00:09:21,790 --> 00:09:23,620
Oh, yeah.

151
00:09:23,620 --> 00:09:25,930
I still don't really get the whole story,

152
00:09:25,930 --> 00:09:28,080
but I'll do anything to help you.

153
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:28,970
Silly.

154
00:09:28,970 --> 00:09:33,540
You're supposed to say, "I'll make the impossible possible with the power of love."

155
00:09:33,540 --> 00:09:36,020
Otherwise you're not a man.

156
00:09:36,020 --> 00:09:36,800
Really?

157
00:09:36,800 --> 00:09:38,130
That's an oxymoron.

158
00:09:38,130 --> 00:09:39,280
It's just appropriate in that situation.

159
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:41,100
That aside, about the other day...

160
00:09:42,010 --> 00:09:44,330
Those bullies went to the same junior high as you, right?

161
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:46,140
H-How did you know that?

162
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:49,440
Well, that's what it sounded like from your conversation.

163
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:52,910
In junior high, someone with authority was helping you,

164
00:09:52,910 --> 00:09:56,810
but since that person's gone now, they started bullying you again.

165
00:09:56,810 --> 00:09:58,340
Oh, what was it?

166
00:09:58,340 --> 00:10:01,240
You still can't find your missing friend?

167
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:04,290
It's Harima Mika-san, right?

168
00:10:06,790 --> 00:10:11,140
It's not that she's been absent,

169
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:14,500
but she never went home until the entrance ceremony.

170
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:16,800
Hey, isn't that something for the cops?

171
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:21,230
She texted me, and she also told her family.

172
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:25,150
It said, "I'm taking a little trip to relax. Please don't worry about me."

173
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,400
A trip to relax?

174
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:27,530
Did something happen?

175
00:10:27,530 --> 00:10:29,160
Well...

176
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,520
Can you listen without getting shocked?

177
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:36,220
Everything in the past few days has made me immune to any kind of shock.

178
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:39,280
Harima-san...

179
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,610
is a stalker.

180
00:10:42,630 --> 00:10:43,940
I see.

181
00:10:43,940 --> 00:10:46,540
So the guy you were badgering with questions the other day...

182
00:10:46,980 --> 00:10:48,650
He's the one being stalked—

183
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:53,340
No, rather, Mika-chan, who wanted to be loved by him but was rejected, took a trip to forget her bitter experience.

184
00:10:54,760 --> 00:10:57,140
It's best to leave it to her family to handle that.

185
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:59,420
If things get worse, they'll call the police.

186
00:11:01,510 --> 00:11:04,180
Were you two good friends?

187
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:06,180
What's up with that question?

188
00:11:07,140 --> 00:11:09,890
Well, we were always together.

189
00:11:09,890 --> 00:11:12,900
He's pretty sharp when it comes to certain things.

190
00:11:12,900 --> 00:11:17,810
I'm really clumsy, and not sociable.

191
00:11:17,810 --> 00:11:21,200
But it was always Mika-san that helped me out.

192
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:24,800
She went as far as going to the same school as I did,

193
00:11:24,800 --> 00:11:27,240
and it felt very awkward for me.

194
00:11:27,240 --> 00:11:28,510
Well...

195
00:11:28,510 --> 00:11:33,050
"She didn't want to let go of you because you made her look better."

196
00:11:33,050 --> 00:11:35,930
Even if you think that, you shouldn't say it out loud, Mikado-kun.

197
00:11:35,930 --> 00:11:37,730
I know.

198
00:11:37,730 --> 00:11:38,460
Know what?

199
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:41,840
That I was just being used by Mika-san to make herself look better.

200
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:45,030
But I was using her too.

201
00:11:45,030 --> 00:11:47,690
It's easier to depend on someone else.

202
00:11:47,690 --> 00:11:50,310
I didn't think I'd be able to live if I didn't.

203
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:56,150
But I don't think I need her anymore.

204
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,950
I got used to it.

205
00:11:57,950 --> 00:12:01,870
I decided to be the class representative

206
00:12:01,870 --> 00:12:05,740
just because she wanted to do it too.

207
00:12:05,740 --> 00:12:08,800
I thought, "At least I can do it in her stead."

208
00:12:09,790 --> 00:12:13,970
I thought, "I can surpass her if I become class rep."

209
00:12:13,970 --> 00:12:16,110
I'm so despicable.

210
00:12:17,420 --> 00:12:20,590
I think it's even more despicable to tell other people about this.

211
00:12:21,800 --> 00:12:25,760
It sounds like you're asking for forgiveness.

212
00:12:26,100 --> 00:12:29,890
Surpassing her is the right decision.

213
00:12:30,210 --> 00:12:34,270
So, why don't you face it straight up?

214
00:12:34,270 --> 00:12:36,980
E-Er...

215
00:12:40,610 --> 00:12:41,990
You're right.

216
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:43,610
Thank you.

217
00:12:44,140 --> 00:12:47,830
I really like this part of him.

218
00:12:51,330 --> 00:12:52,500
Kida-kun!

219
00:12:52,820 --> 00:12:53,880
That's so lame!

220
00:12:53,880 --> 00:12:55,360
Oh, yeah?!

221
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:01,410
What? The strongest in Ikebukuro?

222
00:13:01,410 --> 00:13:03,020
Yes, the strongest.

223
00:13:03,020 --> 00:13:04,470
Are you a journalist?

224
00:13:04,470 --> 00:13:06,250
What do you mean by "strongest"? It sounds so silly.

225
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:09,630
Well, the strongest is the guy on the black bike.

226
00:13:09,630 --> 00:13:10,430
Yeah, I've heard of him.

227
00:13:10,430 --> 00:13:12,270
The headless one, right?

228
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:13,510
You've got to be kidding me!

229
00:13:13,510 --> 00:13:15,940
Oh, and then there's the slasher.

230
00:13:15,940 --> 00:13:17,480
Yeah, him.

231
00:13:18,040 --> 00:13:21,290
But the strongest in this city would be the Dollars.

232
00:13:21,290 --> 00:13:22,110
Dollars?

233
00:13:22,110 --> 00:13:23,990
Yes, Dollars!

234
00:13:24,330 --> 00:13:25,930
My home's the other way.

235
00:13:25,930 --> 00:13:27,940
Thanks for today.

236
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:29,110
See you tomorrow.

237
00:13:29,110 --> 00:13:30,780
Bye-bye, Anri-chan!

238
00:13:31,260 --> 00:13:32,790
I've been thinking...

239
00:13:32,790 --> 00:13:36,580
I think Yagiri-kun and Mika are together.

240
00:13:36,580 --> 00:13:38,390
The victim and the stalker?

241
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:41,690
Like Yagiri-kun has been kidnapped by his stalker.

242
00:13:41,690 --> 00:13:42,550
That makes sense.

243
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:44,080
Searching for someone, eh?

244
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,060
What should we do?

245
00:13:45,060 --> 00:13:46,380
Forget about it.

246
00:13:46,380 --> 00:13:48,070
She said it was fine, right?

247
00:13:48,070 --> 00:13:50,860
I guess it's impossible to find them without the help of an organization or something like that.

248
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:52,560
Like the Dollars.

249
00:13:52,980 --> 00:13:56,850
Mikado... You aren't thinking about joining them, are you?

250
00:13:57,470 --> 00:13:58,850
Of course not.

251
00:13:58,850 --> 00:14:00,640
Seriously, forget about it.

252
00:14:00,640 --> 00:14:03,220
The foolishness of youth makes people join color gangs,

253
00:14:03,220 --> 00:14:05,110
and then they end up regretting it.

254
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:08,610
Yeah, but we're still young.

255
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:16,440
I was really depressed before Mikado came here.

256
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:22,440
I can be this cheerful thanks to a lot of people.

257
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,550
Including Mikado.

258
00:14:25,110 --> 00:14:30,550
He was innocent when he came here, so the heated atmosphere of this city is getting to him.

259
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:33,170
It pains me to see him acting so cautiously.

260
00:14:33,170 --> 00:14:35,530
Well, I could splash some water on him,

261
00:14:35,530 --> 00:14:40,080
but when I see the glimmer in his eyes, I just can't do it.

262
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:43,750
That's why I'm trying to spend as much time as I can with him.

263
00:14:44,690 --> 00:14:49,570
If I could, I'd do anything to prevent him from getting near the dark side of this city.

264
00:14:51,570 --> 00:14:52,550
